@node Intro "Introduction"

                                  @{b}Introduction@{ub}

If you've already run Riktor you will have realised (I would  have  thought)
that it's yet @{i}another@{ui} utility for checking lottery numbers. I know there are
plenty such program already, but most of them seem to include extra features
for  storing  draw  statics  and  the  like.  I  wanted a simple program for
checking the numbers only with the minimum of fuss and so decided  to  write
my  own  program, and here it is. There is little chance Riktor will ever be
updated, although any bugs that become apparent may  be  fixed.  Should  you
find  any bugs or have any queries please do not hesitate to @{"contact me."
Link Author}

Of course any bugs that do exist are  not  actually  my  fault,  you  should
actually  blame  the  @{"beta  testers" Link Credit} because  if there are any bugs, they've
obviously not done their job properly. ;-)

Before you try and use Riktor, please note that it will be necessary for you
to  set the  program @{"tooltypes" Link Config} and edit the @{"Tickets" Link Config} file to suit your own
needs.

Riktor was design for use with the UK lottery. There are no plans to do  any
alternative versions for other countries - Sorry.

@endnode



